# How to Install NGINX on Amazon Linux Using User Data Script

## Step by Step

We will launch an EC2 instance with **Amazon Linux** and automatically install NGINX using **User Data Script**.

After launch:

```text id="3r9q7i"
EC2 starts
→ User Data runs automatically
→ NGINX installs
→ Web server starts
→ Website accessible in browser
```

---

# 🔹 What is Amazon Linux?

Amazon Linux is AWS’s own Linux operating system optimized for EC2.

Popular versions:

✅ Amazon Linux 2
✅ Amazon Linux 2023 (latest)

---

# 🔹 Difference from Ubuntu

| Ubuntu       | Amazon Linux |
| ------------ | ------------ |
| apt          | yum / dnf    |
| ubuntu user  | ec2-user     |
| Debian based | RedHat based |

---

# 🔹 Step 1: Open EC2 Console

Go to:

AWS Console → EC2 → Instances

Click:

```text id="2n2w8k"
Launch Instance
```

---

# 🔹 Step 2: Configure Instance

## Name

Example:

```text id="g6phwp"
amazon-linux-nginx
```

---

## Choose AMI

Select:

```text id="7m37qv"
Amazon Linux 2023 AMI
```

OR Amazon Linux 2.

---

## Instance Type

```text id="uq8m04"
t2.micro
```

(Free tier eligible)

---

## Key Pair

Choose existing OR create new.

Example:

```text id="6o6wqg"
my-key.pem
```

Download key.

---

# 🔹 Step 3: Configure Security Group

Allow:

| Type | Port |
| ---- | ---- |
| SSH  | 22   |
| HTTP | 80   |

Important for browser access.

---

# 🔹 Step 4: Add User Data Script

Scroll down:

```text id="j5iyv7"
Advanced Details
```

Find:

```text id="o4zzul"
User Data
```

Paste this script:

# Amazon Linux 2023

```bash id="lzt06f"
#!/bin/bash

dnf update -y
dnf install nginx -y

systemctl start nginx
systemctl enable nginx

echo "<h1>NGINX Installed on Amazon Linux</h1>" > /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
```

---

# 🔹 For Amazon Linux 2

Use:

```bash id="8k7z4x"
#!/bin/bash

yum update -y
amazon-linux-extras install nginx1 -y

systemctl start nginx
systemctl enable nginx

echo "<h1>NGINX Installed on Amazon Linux 2</h1>" > /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
```

---

# 🔹 What This Script Does

## Shebang

```bash id="v9r4vg"
#!/bin/bash
```

Runs script using bash shell.

---

## Update Packages

Amazon Linux 2023:

```bash id="vdr5to"
dnf update -y
```

Amazon Linux 2:

```bash id="r7dncc"
yum update -y
```

---

## Install NGINX

Amazon Linux 2023:

```bash id="s1mjlwm"
dnf install nginx -y
```

Amazon Linux 2:

```bash id="xjlwm1"
amazon-linux-extras install nginx1 -y
```

---

## Start NGINX

```bash id="pszyd1"
systemctl start nginx
```

Starts web server.

---

## Enable Auto Start

```bash id="xv24r2"
systemctl enable nginx
```

NGINX starts after reboot automatically.

---

## Create Custom HTML Page

```bash id="t4ljq5"
echo "<h1>NGINX Installed on Amazon Linux</h1>" > /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
```

Creates webpage.

---

# 🔹 Step 5: Launch Instance

Click:

```text id="t7l45g"
